The only difference is the order in which the table's font is set and the
columns are packed.
I forgot to mention -- the code you attached does what you described (only the
first column has the custom font) on my computer.
Yep, reproduced your case here too.  It's all the same problem.  The GtkStyle
isn't attached yet when we look up the font description to apply to the other
columns, and depending on the order of events we get messed up.  I'm tweaking up
a fix now.
Fixed > 20050530

Also fixes the equivalent problem with the fonts for TabFolder and Tree.

