Bug.WithStack:
3.1M7
here's a scenario where a hyperlinked symbol stays looking like it's hyperlinked
forever (until the editor closes)

1. create this class
package p;
public class A {
	void mooooooo(){
		mooooooo(); /*1*/
		toString();
	}
}

2. place the caret inside the call in line /*1*/
3. put the mouse over the same symbol and press (and hold) ctrl to activate
hyperlink
4. while holding ctrl, press d (to cut line) and not release the ctrl yet
5. release ctrl after 2 seconds
6. the toString call stays forever hyperlinked!


*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of 50735 ***

